benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/cache - Invalidates the given Cache if specified, otherwise invalidates all caches

covered: Valid Deletion: Successfully invalidate all caches (no cacheName parameter)
Valid Deletion: Successfully invalidate a specific cache by name
Non-Existent Resource: Attempt to invalidate a cache that does not exist
Non-Alive Resource: Attempt to invalidate a cache that exists but is not alive
Empty cacheName parameter: Attempt to invalidate with an empty cacheName parameter
Authorization: Unauthorized access to invalidate caches
Server Error Handling: System error during cache invalidation
No Caches: Invalidate caches when no caches exist
Extra query parameters: Invalidate caches with extra unsupported query parameters
Large cacheName: Invalidate caches with a very large cacheName value
Special characters in cacheName: Invalidate caches with special characters in cacheName
Mixed-case cacheName handling: Invalidate caches with mixed-case cacheName
Performance scenario: Large number of caches (1000) and acceptable response time
Concurrency: Concurrent requests to invalidate all caches
Regression: Previously fixed issue with invalid cacheName format
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets beyond a single large batch.
Rate Limiting: No tests cover rate limiting or throttling behaviors for rapid successive requests.
Caching Headers: No tests verify presence/validation of caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
recommendations: Add tests for explicit pagination behavior when listing/invalidation involves large datasets (e.g., paginated results or batched processing).
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure system stability under bursty DELETE requests.
Add tests to validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on responses and ensure proper caching behavior.
